job.title: Software Engineer Intern
job.description: Role The Software Engineer Intern will aid in gathering new neural network frozen graphs, assembling data sets for each graph, and helping to isolate various blocks within the graphs. As part of these roles, you will be expected to work with machine learning frameworks and associated tools. You will be joining a small team in a dynamic startup environment, where each member is expected to take on a wide range of responsibilities and to learn and grow with the company. Responsibilities Gather frozen graphs for open-source DNNs and associated data sets Modify existing graphical tools to isolate various component sub-graphs Aid in “lowering” the sub-graphs through our toolchain Requirements Pursuing a degree in Computer Engineering or Computer Science Illustrates a strong programming background with Python and Javascript Proficiency with version control software, such as Git Self-driven debugger who loves digging deeper to determine a root cause Nice to haves Experience with Deep Neural Networks Experience with Electron Expected Outcomes in 4 months Collected 3-5 DNN frozen graphs and associated data sets Developed a graphical tool to isolate repeated sub-graphs
